Write a program to get number of values from user until user enter a negative value and store those values in list implementation.

Hint: First create a inner class to define the structure of node. Second create a method called "append()" to insert the values to the list and link the nodes. Third create a print method to print the values in list.

Input Format:
Get input value as integer until user enters a negative value.

Output Format:
Print all list values.

Sample Input:
1
2
3
4
-1

Sample Output:
1 2 3 4 

import java.util.Scanner;

public class Main{
  static class Node {
    int data;
    Node next;

    Node(int data) {
      this.data = data;
      this.next = null;
    }
  }

  static Node head;

  public static void append(int data) {
    Node newNode = new Node(data);
    if (head == null) {
      head = newNode;
      return;
    }

    Node current = head;
    while (current.next != null) {
      current = current.next;
    }
    current.next = newNode;
  }

  public static void printList() {
    Node current = head;
    while (current != null) {
      System.out.print(current.data + " ");
      current = current.next;
    }
  }

  public static void main(String[] args) {
    Scanner scan = new Scanner(System.in);

    int input = scan.nextInt();
    while (input >= 0) {
      append(input);
      input = scan.nextInt();
    }

    printList();
  }
}
